<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1239,1677]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,323,1277,1303]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[592,703,1277,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Aquatica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[592,703,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aquatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with pale yellowish to brown dorsal colouration (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1420,1277,1303]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[212,1341,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[210,1379,172,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Aquatica leii male (17 – 24) and larva (25, 26). 17, 18 dorsal and ventral. 19 – 21 aedeagus left lateral, dorsal and ventral (arrows indicate apical hooked areas on LL). 22 – 24 aedeagal sheath ventral (22, 23) and dorsal (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 25, 26 dorsal and ventral whole body, anterior end to top of page. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1386,1420,1277,1303]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[273,406,1314,1340]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[212,1341,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[210,1379,172,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Aquatica leii male (17 – 24) and larva (25, 26). 17, 18 dorsal and ventral. 19 – 21 aedeagus left lateral, dorsal and ventral (arrows indicate apical hooked areas on LL). 22 – 24 aedeagal sheath ventral (22, 23) and dorsal (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 25, 26 dorsal and ventral whole body, anterior end to top of page. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[332,406,1314,1340]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="20.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.0">
19 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[361,376,1314,1340]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">–</emphasis>
21
</number>
</figureCitation>
) with LL apices inturned and hooked (arrowed in 
<figureCitation box="[992,1125,1314,1340]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[212,1341,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[210,1379,172,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Aquatica leii male (17 – 24) and larva (25, 26). 17, 18 dorsal and ventral. 19 – 21 aedeagus left lateral, dorsal and ventral (arrows indicate apical hooked areas on LL). 22 – 24 aedeagal sheath ventral (22, 23) and dorsal (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 25, 26 dorsal and ventral whole body, anterior end to top of page. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 20, 21</figureCitation>
); lacking teeth along inner basal margins of lateral lobes; aedeagal sheath sternite (
<figureCitation box="[808,942,1351,1378]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[212,1341,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[210,1379,172,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Aquatica leii male (17 – 24) and larva (25, 26). 17, 18 dorsal and ventral. 19 – 21 aedeagus left lateral, dorsal and ventral (arrows indicate apical hooked areas on LL). 22 – 24 aedeagal sheath ventral (22, 23) and dorsal (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 25, 26 dorsal and ventral whole body, anterior end to top of page. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[868,942,1351,1378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">
22 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[898,912,1351,1377]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">–</emphasis>
24
</number>
</figureCitation>
) with both anterior and posterior sections inclining to the right giving the sheath an angulate appearance where these sections join; posterior margin slightly produced and rounded, not emarginate; right margin bearing well defined toothed projection 
<number box="[1397,1408,1427,1453]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1420,1436,1427,1453]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
length from tergite articulations, left side with smaller projection 
<number box="[914,925,1464,1490]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[936,951,1464,1490]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
length from apex. Females macropterous and coloured as for males; bursa bearing paired small fine plates and a single large asymmetrically shaped plate near the entry of the common oviduct. This species was collected in rice fields on the campus of Huazhong Agricultural University. Larvae (
<figureCitation box="[664,800,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[212,1341,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[210,1379,172,1890]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Aquatica leii male (17 – 24) and larva (25, 26). 17, 18 dorsal and ventral. 19 – 21 aedeagus left lateral, dorsal and ventral (arrows indicate apical hooked areas on LL). 22 – 24 aedeagal sheath ventral (22, 23) and dorsal (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 25, 26 dorsal and ventral whole body, anterior end to top of page. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
) have many glandular projections on eversible organs arising along the sides of the body (
<bibRefCitation author="Fu" box="[577,751,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="17" refString="Fu, X. H., Vencl, F. V., Ohba, N., Meyer-Rochow, V. B., Lei, C. L. &amp; Zhang, Z. N. (2007) Structure and function of the eversible glands of the aquatic firefly Luciola leii (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Chemoecology, 17, 117 - 124." type="journal article" year="2007">
Fu 
<emphasis box="[618,671,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[687,751,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Fu and Ballantyne’s 
<figureCitation box="[1017,1087,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 7" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,310,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 7. Aquatica ficta male, female (Fig. 4 only). 2, 4 ventral, 3 dorsal, whole body. 5 aedeagal sheath ventral (arrows indicate lateral projections of margins of sheath sternite). 6, 7 aedeagus dorsal and ventrolateral. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196537/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1072,1087,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
(
<number box="[1103,1167,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2006.0">2006</number>
: 
<number box="[1171,1217,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="343.0">343</number>
) does not indicate the small tooth like projection on the inner right of the aedeagal sheath sternite.
</paragraph>
